Training OfficerA well known and respected resort management company in the Maldives with 6 properties and over 2300 team members is in the process of identifying suitable candidates for the position of Training Officer.Preference will be given to female candidates with previous resort/island and/or cruise ship experience.The right candidate will be able to assist departmental Managers with skills analysis and career planning. Facilitate training as per company standards and resort training needs.
Training consists of both on the job and classroom training and is to be carried out in close co-operation with the relevant Department Heads.
Outgoing, sociable, friendly, courteous, kind and cheerful personality, with an interest in water sports considering an island working/living environmentGood health and fitness given remote location, Contract Term: Two years minimumThe company offers a net salary in the US$ 18k p/a range with a US$ 3k bonus potential, Single accommodation, Laundry services, uniform, Health Insurance, paid sick leave, 1 day off/week, 30 days annual paid vacation leave after completing one year contract. 11 annual public holidays Economy class airfare to report to work/home leaveFor immediate consideration please submit your updated resume incl. a recent photo to my attention.Heinz@cha-international.com
